The paper discusses a system that uses evolutionary optimization to create effective web interface designs for conversion optimization. This involves designing interfaces that encourage users to take a desired action, such as registering or purchasing. The paper also discusses the use of A/B testing and multivariate testing in conversion optimization. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
